body:
# Tailwind CSS v4

Released January 22, 2025. A ground-up rewrite with CSS-first configuration and massive performance improvements.

## Identifying v3 vs v4

| Signal | v3 | v4 |
|--------|----|----|  
| Config file | `tailwind.config.js` exists | No config file (or `@config` for compat) |
| CSS imports | `@tailwind base/components/utilities` | `@import "tailwindcss"` |
| Content config | `content: [...]` in config | Automatic detection |
| PostCSS plugin | `tailwindcss` | `@tailwindcss/postcss` |
| Theme customization | JS `theme.extend` | CSS `@theme {}` |
| Color format | RGB hex | OKLCH |
| Gradient classes | `bg-gradient-to-r` | `bg-linear-to-r` |
| Container queries | `@tailwindcss/container-queries` plugin | Built-in `@container` |

## Performance

| Metric | v3.4 | v4.0 | Speedup |
|--------|------|------|---------|
| Full build | 378ms | 100ms | 3.78x |
| Incremental (new CSS) | 44ms | 5ms | 8.8x |
| Incremental (no new CSS) | 35ms | 192us | 182x |

## New Directives

### @import
Single entry point replaces three @tailwind directives:
```css
/* v3 */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

/* v4 */
@import "tailwindcss";
```

### @theme
CSS-first configuration replaces tailwind.config.js:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-brand: oklch(0.6 0.2 260);
  --font-display: "Cal Sans", sans-serif;
  --breakpoint-3xl: 120rem;
  --ease-snappy: cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1);

  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.3s ease-out;
  @keyframes fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
}
```

Theme variables become CSS custom properties on `:root` AND generate utility classes.

### @utility
Custom utilities with full variant support:
```css
@utility content-auto {
  content-visibility: auto;
}
```

### @custom-variant
Custom variants without JavaScript:
```css
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
@custom-variant hocus (&:hover, &:focus);
```

### @source
Explicitly add content detection paths:
```css
@source "../node_modules/@my-company/ui-lib";
```

### @plugin
Load legacy JS plugins:
```css
@plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
@plugin "./my-custom-plugin.js";
```

### @reference
Import types without emitting CSS (for scoped styles):
```vue
<style>
  @reference "tailwindcss";
  h1 { @apply text-2xl font-bold; }
</style>
```

## New Features

### Built-in Container Queries
```html
<div class="@container">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 @sm:grid-cols-3 @lg:grid-cols-4">
    Responds to container, not viewport
  </div>
</div>
```

### Max-Width Breakpoint Variants
```html
<div class="flex flex-row max-md:flex-col">
  Row by default, column below 768px
</div>
```

### 3D Transforms
```html
<div class="perspective-distant">
  <div class="rotate-x-51 rotate-z-43 transform-3d">
    3D transformed element
  </div>
</div>
```

### Expanded Gradients
```html
<!-- Angled linear gradients -->
<div class="bg-linear-45 from-blue-500 to-purple-500" />

<!-- Color interpolation -->
<div class="bg-linear-to-r/oklch from-indigo-500 to-teal-400" />

<!-- Conic & radial -->
<div class="bg-conic from-red-500 to-blue-500" />
<div class="bg-radial-[at_25%_25%] from-white to-zinc-900" />
```

### New Utilities
- `not-hover:opacity-75` — negate any variant
- `inset-shadow-*`, `inset-ring-*` — stackable shadow layers
- `field-sizing-content` — auto-resize textareas without JS
- `color-scheme-dark` — scrollbar dark mode
- `font-stretch-*` — variable font width
- `starting:opacity-0` — @starting-style for entry animations
- `in-*` — group-like variant without `group` class
- `nth-*` — :nth-child selectors

### OKLCH Color Palette
All default colors migrated from sRGB to OKLCH for wider gamut on modern displays:
```css
/* v4 default */
--color-blue-500: oklch(62.3% 0.214 259.815);
/* v3 was hex/rgb */
```

### Cascade Layers
v4 uses native CSS cascade layers for predictable specificity:
```css
@layer theme, base, components, utilities;
```

## Migration from v3

### Automated Upgrade Tool
```bash
npx @tailwindcss/upgrade
```

This handles most mechanical changes automatically.

### Manual Migration Checklist

1. **Install new packages**
   ```bash
   npm install tailwindcss@latest @tailwindcss/postcss
   npm uninstall postcss-import autoprefixer
   ```

2. **Update PostCSS config**
   ```javascript
   // postcss.config.js
   export default { plugins: ["@tailwindcss/postcss"] };
   ```

3. **Replace CSS entry**
   ```css
   /* Remove @tailwind directives, add: */
   @import "tailwindcss";
   ```

4. **Move theme to CSS**
   ```css
   /* Move tailwind.config.js theme.extend to: */
   @theme {
     --color-brand: #4f46e5;
     --font-display: "Cal Sans", sans-serif;
   }
   ```

5. **Move plugins to @plugin**
   ```css
   @plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
   @plugin "@tailwindcss/forms";
   ```

6. **Remove content config** — v4 auto-detects

7. **Rename utilities**
   - `bg-gradient-to-r` → `bg-linear-to-r`
   - `bg-opacity-50` → `bg-black/50` (modifier syntax)

8. **Delete tailwind.config.js** (once migrated)

### Breaking Changes Summary

| Change | v3 | v4 |
|--------|----|----|  
| Config format | JavaScript | CSS @theme |
| CSS entry | `@tailwind` directives | `@import "tailwindcss"` |
| Content config | Required | Auto-detected |
| PostCSS plugin | `tailwindcss` | `@tailwindcss/postcss` |
| Color space | sRGB | OKLCH |
| Gradient prefix | `bg-gradient-*` | `bg-linear-*` |
| Opacity utilities | `bg-opacity-50` | `bg-black/50` modifier |
| Container queries | Plugin | Built-in |
| Dark mode config | `darkMode: "class"` | `@custom-variant dark (...)` |
| PostCSS imports | `postcss-import` needed | Built-in |
| Autoprefixer | Required | Not needed |

## Keeping v3 Compatibility

If you can't migrate everything at once, use `@config` to load a v3 config:
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@config "../../tailwind.config.js";
```
